[SN]TITLE[SN]
Ashford biker Michael Waldman killed in Netherfield crash

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A motorcyclist who was killed in a collision during a group ride in East Sussex has been named by police.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Michael Waldman, 53, Ashford, Kent, suffered fatal injuries when his Kawasaki ZX-6R collided with a Seat Ibiza on the B2096 near Netherfield.
He was travelling towards Battle with three other motorcyclists at the time of the crash on Sunday.
The driver of the Seat, a 30-year-old woman from Sedlescombe, was not hurt in the incident.
